Pat pork dry and season with salt and pepper. Heat oil in a large frypan over high heat and brown pork on all sides - about 5 minutes. Add LACTAID(R) Fat Free Milk and simmer, covered, for 2 hours. Continue to cook pork, partially covered, at a bare simmer until very tender, about 1 hour. Put pork on a cutting board and let stand 5 minutes. Season cooking liquid with salt, pepper and garlic powder and boil for 2 minutes. Thinly slice pork and pour cooking liquid on top.